WEBVTT

00:02.458 --> 00:06.041
SAM: <i>Time travel.</i>
<i>It sounds so science fictiony,</i>

00:06.041 --> 00:08.709
<i>but in a way,</i>
<i>we travel through time every day.</i>

00:08.709 --> 00:11.875
<i>A childhood memory</i>
<i>can instantly pull you into the past.</i>

00:11.875 --> 00:14.625
<i>A wish can send you</i>
<i>zooming into the future.</i>

00:14.625 --> 00:18.333
<i>And what's actually hard</i>
<i>is to stay planted in the present,</i>

00:18.333 --> 00:20.375
<i>to be here in the now.</i>

00:20.375 --> 00:21.834
I wanna go home now.

00:21.834 --> 00:24.417
Calm down, you're fine.

00:24.417 --> 00:28.041
Mom, a brain doctor does not call
and say that he has to see you

00:28.041 --> 00:30.417
unless there's something
seriously wrong, okay?

00:30.417 --> 00:32.208
You are not dying.
You're not even warm.

00:32.208 --> 00:36.291
If I slip into a coma again,
do not unplug anything, okay?

00:36.291 --> 00:39.375
Not a machine, not a radio, nothing.

00:41.291 --> 00:43.625
- There's my favorite patient.
- Hi.

00:44.000 --> 00:45.542
I bet your ears have been burning.

00:45.542 --> 00:46.709
Huh?

00:46.709 --> 00:50.458
Um, yeah, they kind of--
They have. Maybe, sort of. Is that bad?

00:50.458 --> 00:53.750
Oh, no, no, no. It just means people
have been talking about you.

00:54.291 --> 00:56.500
Okay, now the reason
I called you here...

00:57.500 --> 01:00.959
Aw. It's strange not having
our weekly appointments, isn't it?

01:01.917 --> 01:03.792
They were like little dates for me.

01:03.792 --> 01:06.917
Doctor, please. Do you mind?
I can't stand this. Is she dying or not?

01:06.917 --> 01:10.250
Oh, no, no, no. We want her
to be part of a clinical trial.

01:10.250 --> 01:11.458
Hm?

01:11.458 --> 01:13.166
ANDY: We are close
to getting the FDA approval

01:13.166 --> 01:15.959
for a new drug that will help people
with various forms of memory loss.

01:16.750 --> 01:18.583
Oh. Oh, wow.

01:18.583 --> 01:19.792
- That's it?
- Mm-hm.

01:19.792 --> 01:22.959
Wow. I mean, you could've just left that
on the machine.

01:22.959 --> 01:24.792
Oh, he did, I forgot.

01:32.250 --> 01:35.625
See, this is the side of the brain
where the memory is.

01:35.625 --> 01:38.500
It's a very exclusive study.

01:38.500 --> 01:40.750
Because, apparently,
I am one of very few

01:40.750 --> 01:43.500
high-functioning amnesiacs
in the entire country.

01:43.500 --> 01:47.500
Yeah, said the girl
wearing black shoes and brown pants.

01:47.500 --> 01:49.959
You know what? Sometimes Einstein
left the house naked.

01:49.959 --> 01:51.792
How much are you getting paid for this?

01:51.792 --> 01:54.041
There's a guy in Texas
who got paid 25 grand

01:54.041 --> 01:55.834
to have his foot cut off and reattached.

01:55.834 --> 01:57.583
Ooh. I'd do that for thirteen-five.

01:58.583 --> 02:00.125
It's not about money, guys.

02:00.125 --> 02:03.583
I just wanna help people, you know.
And I wanna know that I helped people.

02:03.583 --> 02:05.750
And I kind of want people
to know that I helped people.

02:06.291 --> 02:09.083
Oh, did I mention
that they might call it the Newly Report?

02:09.083 --> 02:12.000
- So, what's it feel like?
- Well, feels like nothing right now

02:12.000 --> 02:13.875
because I took the pill
about an hour ago.

02:13.875 --> 02:15.208
Maybe you have the placebo.

02:15.750 --> 02:18.458
No. No, I don't wanna be the placebo.

02:18.458 --> 02:19.834
[KNOCKING ON GLASS]

02:23.625 --> 02:26.458
You're not supposed
to remember anything that they-- Oh, jeez.

02:26.458 --> 02:27.959
[CRYING]

02:27.959 --> 02:30.250
What are you crying about?
You scared the crap out of me.

02:31.709 --> 02:34.166
- Nope, not the placebo.
DENA: You just had one.

02:34.166 --> 02:35.875
What was it? Was it about me?

02:35.875 --> 02:40.125
No. No, it was just some kids
and balloons and stuff. It was really nice.

02:40.125 --> 02:41.875
Dr. Andy wants me to write this down.

02:41.875 --> 02:43.875
- Free notebook. Score.
- Yeah.

02:44.667 --> 02:46.375
[CAR ALARM WAILING]

02:49.250 --> 02:50.875
ANDREA: Um, Sam.
- Yeah.

02:50.875 --> 02:53.250
The guy we hate is parked over there.

02:53.250 --> 02:55.250
[LAUGHING]

02:55.458 --> 02:56.750
Oh, well.

02:56.750 --> 02:58.250
I'm sure this guy did something wrong.

02:58.792 --> 03:01.041
Oh. Okey-dokey. Heh, heh.

03:01.041 --> 03:04.625
These are coming on a little strong,
so I think I'm gonna just go lay down.

03:05.875 --> 03:09.792
- Okay, well, feel better.
- Thanks. Bye, you guys.

03:10.333 --> 03:11.709
Oh, that poor bird.

03:14.417 --> 03:16.291
Well, hello there.

03:16.291 --> 03:17.458
Hello yourself.

03:18.500 --> 03:19.750
And who do you belong to?

03:19.750 --> 03:21.959
- They're mine. They belong to me.
- They're mine.

03:21.959 --> 03:24.458
They're mine, mine, mine. I love them.

03:24.458 --> 03:26.166
Oh, lucky dogs.

03:26.166 --> 03:28.083
You have two mommies
fighting over you.

03:28.083 --> 03:29.959
[LAUGHING]

03:31.875 --> 03:33.959
He thinks we're a couple.
That's so funny.

03:33.959 --> 03:36.542
- That's not funny.
- It's a little funny, you know.

03:36.542 --> 03:38.625
Maybe you should be Mom,
and I should be Mommy.

03:38.625 --> 03:40.083
I don't wanna confuse them.

03:46.625 --> 03:48.750
- Hey, Frank.
- Miss Newly.

03:49.542 --> 03:52.291
Morning, ma'am.
I'm Frank, the new doorman.

03:52.291 --> 03:54.500
I wanna say what a pleasure it is
to meet you.

03:54.500 --> 03:58.625
Shh. Okay, here's what I need:
Hold the door for me, hail my cabs,

03:58.625 --> 04:01.959
and I don't like guys who send flowers
so you could just throw those out.

04:01.959 --> 04:04.375
You do all that, Hank,
and you might keep your job.

04:05.750 --> 04:08.959
Yes, Miss Newly.

04:08.959 --> 04:11.166
I'm sorry, Frank.

04:17.542 --> 04:19.375
- Hey.
- Hey.

04:19.625 --> 04:21.750
- What's wrong?
- Nothing. Oh, I lucked out.

04:21.750 --> 04:25.291
I got to be part of this, um, study
for memory recovery.

04:25.291 --> 04:27.125
You have crazy eyes.
Part of the study?

04:27.125 --> 04:28.834
I don't know. I'm not a scientist, so...

04:29.375 --> 04:30.583
Will you be okay alone?

04:30.583 --> 04:33.041
Because I was gonna head out
and look at an apartment.

04:33.041 --> 04:35.000
What? What happened
to the one from yesterday?

04:35.000 --> 04:36.834
- It had a view.
- Well, it also had a smell.

04:37.500 --> 04:39.583
There was a goat's head
in the refrigerator.

04:39.583 --> 04:42.125
- Plus, somebody beat me to it.
- Well, I hope you get this one.

04:43.333 --> 04:44.542
I mean, for you.

04:44.542 --> 04:49.500
I mean, I know it's been really weird
living here, you know, for you.

04:49.500 --> 04:50.750
And me.

04:50.750 --> 04:52.333
For us.

04:52.333 --> 04:54.000
Mostly for you.

04:54.250 --> 04:56.000
And me.

04:56.959 --> 04:59.000
- I'll let you know.
- Okay.

04:59.583 --> 05:01.208
Goodbye.

05:01.625 --> 05:02.750
Goodbye.

05:07.125 --> 05:10.000
Almost there. Almost there.

05:11.333 --> 05:13.291
Okay, almost there.

05:15.583 --> 05:16.709
Almost there.

05:19.667 --> 05:21.083
[TIRES SCREECH]

05:22.375 --> 05:25.500
Mommy, can I come home tonight?

05:26.417 --> 05:29.125
Well, what time
is your dinner party over?

05:31.625 --> 05:36.000
And here you go, all set for the night.

05:36.000 --> 05:40.959
- Got your notebook and your pills.
SAM: Thank you.

05:40.959 --> 05:43.125
And a wave machine.

05:43.125 --> 05:45.166
I got this for your father
on his last birthday,

05:45.166 --> 05:47.291
but it made him have to tinkle all night.

05:47.291 --> 05:49.208
I'm sorry I'm being
such a baby about this.

05:49.208 --> 05:53.917
It's just that these memories are so vivid,
you know, like, stepping off the curb

05:53.917 --> 05:57.333
and I was crying for some reason,
and these brakes were--

05:57.333 --> 05:58.542
[SIGHS]

05:58.542 --> 06:01.333
I was wearing
this very bright green jacket.

06:01.333 --> 06:04.834
It's probably a blessing in disguise.
That jacket never looked good on you.

06:06.250 --> 06:10.542
Anyway, maybe I'm just skimming
the bad ones off the top, you know,

06:10.542 --> 06:12.917
so I can get down to the good ones.

06:12.917 --> 06:15.291
Kind of like that skin
that forms on the top of pudding,

06:15.291 --> 06:17.625
and underneath
it's just chocolaty goodness.

06:18.125 --> 06:19.542
Ah.

06:19.542 --> 06:21.750
There are memories
I'd love to have back.

06:21.750 --> 06:23.333
Like that summer before I had you.

06:24.417 --> 06:26.125
Yeah, thanks.

06:26.917 --> 06:28.125
Mom.

06:28.125 --> 06:30.667
I had a great body that summer.

06:30.667 --> 06:32.083
Fine. Well, you know what?

06:32.083 --> 06:36.709
Don't come crying to me when,
you know, you come crying to me, okay.

06:36.709 --> 06:38.917
All right, all right. Fine.
Good night, sleep tight.

06:40.250 --> 06:41.875
Oh, ha, ha.

06:41.875 --> 06:44.875
Pill's working already,
I just remembered Todd called,

06:44.875 --> 06:46.583
and he said he's got a new apartment.

06:46.583 --> 06:49.667
Really, he found an apartment? Wow.

06:49.667 --> 06:53.500
- That's what you wanted, right?
- Yeah. Yeah. No, it's just that he did it.

06:53.500 --> 06:56.750
It's just so not Todd.

07:01.083 --> 07:02.625
- Cute.
- Well, you look nice.

07:02.625 --> 07:05.750
- Thanks.
- You have any place special in mind?

07:05.750 --> 07:09.625
Yeah, actually,
there's this cute place off I-90 West.

07:09.625 --> 07:11.792
I-90. Wait.

07:11.792 --> 07:14.750
So our first date is really
me giving you a ride to the airport?

07:14.750 --> 07:16.458
We have three hours.

07:16.458 --> 07:18.250
You're lucky there's fog in New York.

07:20.083 --> 07:21.500
What are you doing?

07:22.291 --> 07:25.959
There must be men who put up with
this stuff for you or you wouldn't even try.

07:26.250 --> 07:27.291
Good night.

07:27.625 --> 07:29.166
Don't be a jerk.

07:29.542 --> 07:32.041
You know what,
your not giving a girl a ride to the airport

07:32.041 --> 07:34.417
says something about your manners.

07:40.208 --> 07:41.959
Can you believe
that Todd hasn't called?

07:41.959 --> 07:45.333
I mean, who is he to not call me?
I mean, I'm the one who doesn't call him.

07:45.333 --> 07:47.208
What do you care? Forget about him.

07:47.208 --> 07:49.250
No, you're right, you're right. I'm done.

07:49.250 --> 07:51.625
- Wanna go to the bar?
- Do you know what he drives?

07:51.625 --> 07:54.500
I was just rejected
by a guy whose windows zipper.

07:54.500 --> 07:58.166
Well, that guy over there owns a jet,
two buildings and three senators.

07:58.166 --> 08:00.792
I mean, I practically apologized to him,
and he ignores me?

08:00.792 --> 08:03.291
Oh, nah-uh. No, no, no.

08:03.291 --> 08:06.250
No, he does not get to choose.

08:06.917 --> 08:08.917
[MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

08:14.375 --> 08:16.250
Hello, Todd.

08:17.417 --> 08:18.834
- You.
- Mm-hm.

08:19.125 --> 08:21.333
I thought I was hired
to photograph a kid's party.

08:21.333 --> 08:24.250
Well, what was I supposed to do?
You wouldn't return my phone calls.

08:25.000 --> 08:27.500
Man, I should've gotten it
when I saw it was this building.

08:27.500 --> 08:31.500
You're Mrs. Butterworth.

08:31.500 --> 08:34.917
Yeah, well, I don't know anybody
named "Missis." And so what?

08:35.291 --> 08:37.291
You can take pictures of me now.

08:37.291 --> 08:40.083
Naked or whatever,
I'm very cooperative.

08:40.375 --> 08:41.417
Wow.

08:41.792 --> 08:43.792
- What?
- Well, you went to a lot of trouble

08:43.792 --> 08:45.959
to get me here, you're really into me.

08:46.667 --> 08:48.667
- Shut up.
- You are.

08:48.667 --> 08:51.166
Why don't you put on some clothes,
we'll go get some food.

08:51.166 --> 08:53.583
I mean, unless you've never done it
in that order before.

08:54.834 --> 08:56.500
Jerk.

09:00.458 --> 09:03.458
Just let me put on some jeans.

09:05.792 --> 09:07.750
[GROANING]

09:12.458 --> 09:14.458
Ooh. Bad night?

09:14.458 --> 09:15.709
Awful.

09:15.709 --> 09:19.500
Just all night long,
just more bad things that I did.

09:19.500 --> 09:22.792
Bad, and bad, bad,
then I had to get up to pee,

09:22.792 --> 09:25.500
you know, more bad, and bad, pee,

09:25.500 --> 09:29.375
turned off that wave machine,
and just bad.

09:29.834 --> 09:32.083
- Montpelier.
- I'm sorry?

09:32.083 --> 09:34.667
Capital of Vermont.
I can never remember that one.

09:34.667 --> 09:36.000
These pills are great.

09:36.000 --> 09:38.875
Oh, yeah,
they're like a party in my head.

09:43.625 --> 09:46.583
You know what it does to me
when you wear that skirt.

09:46.583 --> 09:47.959
[DENA MOANS]

09:47.959 --> 09:49.458
She's kidding.

09:49.458 --> 09:51.458
Stop it. Why are you doing this?

09:51.458 --> 09:54.542
Because you actually hate that
people think you're gay. It's too fun.

09:54.542 --> 09:58.291
I don't care if someone thinks I'm gay.
I care if they think I'm with you.

09:58.291 --> 10:00.875
- No offense.
- In what world is that no offense?

10:00.875 --> 10:03.667
I'm just saying, if I were gay,
I would be with someone else.

10:03.667 --> 10:05.959
- Like who?
- I haven't thought about it.

10:05.959 --> 10:07.000
Like for instance.

10:07.291 --> 10:09.375
I don't know. Carol in Payroll.

10:09.375 --> 10:13.583
Oh! Not in a million years could you get
hot lesbian Carol from Payroll.

10:13.583 --> 10:15.250
Hey, I can get anyone I want.

10:15.250 --> 10:17.834
I am the hottest lesbian
that's not a lesbian in the entire world.

10:20.291 --> 10:22.333
I don't know how much longer
I can do this, Mom.

10:22.333 --> 10:26.333
I wanna help people and all, but I just--
I feel like such a loser.

10:26.333 --> 10:28.875
Sweetie, listen to me.

10:29.166 --> 10:32.041
Listen, I saw this article...

10:32.667 --> 10:35.625
Oh, Lord that was five years ago.
I'm a genius.

10:36.041 --> 10:39.583
Oh, anyway,
about how the mind protects us

10:39.583 --> 10:42.458
and only allows us to recall
as much as we can handle.

10:43.208 --> 10:46.959
So if you're remembering
really bad things about yourself,

10:46.959 --> 10:50.125
just imagine how truly awful
the things you're not remembering are.

10:52.083 --> 10:54.500
Yeah. I'm all better.

10:54.500 --> 10:56.166
Thanks, that's great.

10:56.166 --> 10:57.500
[RINGS]

10:59.166 --> 11:01.250
- Hello.
- Samantha.

11:01.250 --> 11:04.041
Oh, it's nice to hear your voice.

11:04.709 --> 11:07.333
How did you, uh, do last night?

11:07.333 --> 11:09.709
Actually, doctor,
I had a really rough time.

11:09.709 --> 11:12.333
Um, these pills are really something.

11:12.709 --> 11:14.291
Aren't they? Heh, heh.

11:14.291 --> 11:17.208
Why don't you go ahead
and throw those away. Just toss them.

11:17.208 --> 11:19.959
Uh, well, if you're sure.

11:19.959 --> 11:22.208
The drug company
is suspending the trial.

11:22.208 --> 11:25.917
<i>It's no biggie just a few people</i>
<i>reporting some tiny side effects.</i>

11:26.959 --> 11:29.083
Well, gosh, you know, I just feel terrible.

11:29.083 --> 11:32.750
I mean, I guess I'm just gonna have
to do good for people some other time.

11:32.750 --> 11:35.000
I feel terrible too.

11:36.000 --> 11:38.250
Maybe we could, uh,
make our own memory.

11:38.250 --> 11:40.041
Yeah, okay, bye.

11:41.500 --> 11:43.000
Bye.

11:47.583 --> 11:49.166
What was that?

11:49.417 --> 11:50.667
No, no, no. What was that?

11:50.667 --> 11:52.625
No, that was a good one.
That was a good one.

11:52.625 --> 11:57.291
I need another pill. Oh, no.

11:58.458 --> 12:02.500
I just need one more pill.
You gotta hook me up, doc.

12:02.500 --> 12:05.667
- Samantha, there are no more pills.
- Don't tell me that, man.

12:05.667 --> 12:08.625
I need a slam. I need a bang.
I need a pop.

12:08.625 --> 12:10.333
I think you might be making up slang.

12:10.333 --> 12:12.667
I just need one more, okay?

12:12.667 --> 12:16.625
I started to get pieces of this
really, really cool memory about-- Of--

12:18.208 --> 12:19.875
- Oh, no, shoot.
- Of us?

12:19.875 --> 12:21.333
- Was it us?
- No. Damn it.

12:21.333 --> 12:22.750
What's going on?

12:22.750 --> 12:24.959
- Am I losing my memories now?
- No.

12:24.959 --> 12:26.500
That's a funny story. Yes, you are.

12:27.417 --> 12:29.458
But only the new memories
brought on by the drug.

12:29.959 --> 12:34.792
So all these new memories that I'm having
are just gonna be gone, like, forever?

12:34.792 --> 12:36.500
As soon as the drug
leaves your system, yes.

12:36.959 --> 12:39.792
But if there is any changes in the trial,
I will call you.

12:40.250 --> 12:43.125
- I'd like to call you anyway--
- It was something important though.

12:43.125 --> 12:44.792
And I need to know what.

12:46.750 --> 12:48.333
- Come here. Come here.
- What? Thanks.

12:48.917 --> 12:50.667
Oh, there we-- Ah.

12:53.625 --> 12:55.959
SAM: I gotta run. I have
a thousand meetings to get to.

12:55.959 --> 12:57.667
- I'll see you later, okay?
- Okay.

12:57.667 --> 12:59.709
- Bye.
- Bye.

13:01.000 --> 13:02.959
- What are you doing?
- No, I'm not letting go

13:02.959 --> 13:06.041
- until you give me a real hug.
- Ugh, my God, you are such a girl.

13:06.041 --> 13:07.375
Here.

13:07.792 --> 13:09.458
- No. Look at your shoulders.
- What?

13:10.125 --> 13:12.333
They're way up here. Drop them.

13:12.333 --> 13:14.166
Drop them more.

13:14.166 --> 13:15.834
There you go.

13:17.208 --> 13:19.166
I hate you.

13:19.583 --> 13:21.667
I just had another one. About Todd.

13:21.667 --> 13:23.875
Oh, Todd. Yay.

13:24.250 --> 13:26.333
Oh, but it's just gonna go away, isn't it?

13:26.333 --> 13:28.166
[MUMBLING INDISTINCTLY]

13:28.166 --> 13:30.166
No? We can do it later.

13:32.417 --> 13:35.500
Carol. Heh, heh, heh.

13:35.500 --> 13:39.458
DENA: Oh, hey.
CAROL: Oh, Dena, hi.

13:39.458 --> 13:42.834
Hi, just bringing Chase some lunch
and checking in.

13:42.834 --> 13:45.667
His new assistant
sounds a little too pretty on the phone.

13:45.667 --> 13:46.875
[LAUGHING]

13:46.875 --> 13:49.041
People tell me
I have a beautiful phone voice.

13:49.041 --> 13:52.000
Oh, Joan Didion. I love her.

13:52.000 --> 13:53.917
- Andrea Belladonna's office.
CAROL: So do I.

13:53.917 --> 13:57.125
You know, I just finished
reading <i>Slouching Towards Bethlehem</i>,

13:57.125 --> 13:59.458
and now I'm going back
to reread <i>Play It As It Lays.</i>

13:59.458 --> 14:00.792
Oh.

14:00.792 --> 14:02.625
I love your blouse.

14:02.625 --> 14:04.041
Mine's kind of tight.

14:04.041 --> 14:08.959
It keeps opening. See it, it's open.
It's open.

14:09.625 --> 14:11.083
- Okay.
ANDREA: That shirt thing worked

14:11.083 --> 14:13.625
three times last Christmas party.

14:14.083 --> 14:16.291
These things work. They work.

14:20.500 --> 14:22.500
[PHONE RINGS]

14:22.834 --> 14:24.500
SAM [ON RECORDING]:
<i>Hey, this is Sam.</i>

14:24.500 --> 14:26.417
TODD:<i> And Todd.</i>
SAM: <i>What--? What are you doing?</i>

14:26.417 --> 14:28.166
TODD: <i>I live here. I get my name</i>
<i>on the machine.</i>

14:28.166 --> 14:31.041
SAM:<i> No, no, that's not part of the deal.</i>
TODD:<i> Our phone line, our machine.</i>

14:31.041 --> 14:34.917
SAM: <i>Oh, my God, why don't you</i>
<i>just stamp "Property of Todd" on my ass.</i>

14:34.917 --> 14:38.333
<i>Or better yet, why don't you go ahead</i>
<i>and absorb me like an evil twin.</i>

14:38.333 --> 14:39.667
[ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS]

14:41.041 --> 14:42.458
What?

14:57.500 --> 15:00.125
What? Did you not pay the electric bill?

15:00.125 --> 15:01.834
Todd, I asked you to do one thing.

15:04.000 --> 15:05.500
What are you doing? Get up.

15:05.500 --> 15:07.000
Sam.

15:11.333 --> 15:12.375
He proposed.

15:15.458 --> 15:18.166
Cut it out, all right.
Things are good the way they are.

15:18.166 --> 15:21.959
- They are, it's why I want more.
- We live together, Todd.

15:21.959 --> 15:24.875
That's more than I've given to anyone.
You should just say thanks.

15:25.500 --> 15:27.333
That should be a thank you ring.

15:28.333 --> 15:30.667
This is where you push me away
because you're scared.

15:30.667 --> 15:34.125
- Do not tell me how I'm feeling.
- I'm trying to tell you I love you.

15:34.125 --> 15:36.041
Yeah, well, if you did,
you wouldn't do this.

15:36.041 --> 15:38.625
You're right, forget it.

15:38.959 --> 15:40.834
Big mistake.

15:41.875 --> 15:44.834
There. Never happened. Better?

15:44.834 --> 15:47.000
Now you're gonna try
to make me feel bad about it?

15:47.000 --> 15:50.208
Feel however you want, Sam,
you always do.

15:50.208 --> 15:52.000
Goodbye.

15:53.083 --> 15:55.000
Nice. Very romantic.

15:55.500 --> 15:57.208
Hey, give me a pen.
Give me a pen, please.

15:57.208 --> 15:59.291
- I don't have a pen.

15:57.208 --> 16:01.709
- You have to have a pen.

15:59.291 --> 16:01.709
- Wait. Here. Have a lipstick.

16:01.709 --> 16:03.542
Oh, God. Oh, my God. It was me.

16:03.542 --> 16:07.458
I was the scaredy-cat,
and now I'm pushing him away again.

16:07.458 --> 16:08.875
Oh, my God, I have to stop him.

16:08.875 --> 16:10.834
What is this, tangerine? It's nice.

16:10.834 --> 16:12.875
WOMAN: Keep it.
- Thanks. Okay.

16:17.083 --> 16:19.583
Hey, Todd, it's me. Pick up, pick up.

16:19.583 --> 16:21.792
Listen, I'm on my way
back to the apartment,

16:21.792 --> 16:26.125
I remember the proposal,
so please don't go, we really have to talk.

16:26.333 --> 16:31.208
Proposal, proposal, proposal.

16:31.208 --> 16:33.458
Do not talk to me, Frank.
Proposal, proposal.

16:33.458 --> 16:35.500
Always my first choice.

16:40.917 --> 16:44.375
I tried. I did everything I could,
and it's not enough.

16:44.375 --> 16:46.917
You do not get to choose
when we break up.

16:46.917 --> 16:48.542
I just did.

16:52.500 --> 16:55.250
Yeah, I just cut it all off.

16:55.250 --> 16:58.208
Todd loved my hair long,
that'll teach him.

16:58.208 --> 16:59.667
[TIRES SCREECH]

17:00.750 --> 17:02.750
Oh, hey, hey. Listen--

17:02.750 --> 17:05.417
I found a place. Soon as they
process the application, I'm in.

17:05.417 --> 17:07.542
- Listen.
- It's not big, it's a little dark,

17:07.542 --> 17:10.417
but there is zero goat heads,
and I'm feeling pretty good about that.

17:10.417 --> 17:11.750
Listen. We need to talk.

17:11.750 --> 17:16.125
I just need you to know
that I am so sorry that I...

17:18.250 --> 17:19.291
That I what?

17:20.667 --> 17:24.291
Oh. Oh, it's here. It's here. Um, I--
For the pro--

17:24.917 --> 17:26.125
"Pro--"

17:26.125 --> 17:28.250
[SAM STAMMERING]

17:28.250 --> 17:29.625
Um...

17:29.625 --> 17:30.917
Pro-- It's smeared.

17:31.583 --> 17:34.083
Propun-- Does any of that ring a bell?

17:34.083 --> 17:36.333
You know what, hold on,
there's a message.

17:36.583 --> 17:38.417
SAM [ON RECORDING]:
<i>Hey, Todd, it's me.</i>

17:38.417 --> 17:40.208
<i>Pick up, pick up.</i>
<i>Listen, I'm on my way--</i>

17:43.542 --> 17:44.959
Well, you're here now, what was it?

17:46.458 --> 17:49.250
- I don't know. It's gone.
- Well, I'm sure it'll come back.

17:50.250 --> 17:51.625
No. It won't.

17:53.750 --> 17:55.125
Maybe it was nothing.

18:15.250 --> 18:17.333
Oh, hi.

18:17.667 --> 18:20.250
Just reading a little Didion, like usual.

18:20.250 --> 18:23.208
There's nothing like a poignant
and trenchant look

18:23.208 --> 18:26.500
at marriage in the 21st century,
says the New York-- Me.

18:26.500 --> 18:30.250
- Why are you stalking me?
- What? I-- I'm not.

18:30.250 --> 18:32.291
I know that you keep calling me
and hanging up.

18:32.291 --> 18:35.417
- Your extension shows up on my phone.
- It does?

18:36.250 --> 18:40.000
I call everyone in the office just to say hi.
Okay, why don't you like me?

18:40.000 --> 18:41.041
Excuse me?

18:44.959 --> 18:47.875
- Kiss me. Kiss me. Just do it.
- Okay, that's it.

18:48.375 --> 18:50.750
You just bought yourself
a sit-down with Human Resources.

18:50.750 --> 18:53.208
- No.
- Oh, wait. Wait, Carol.

18:53.208 --> 18:56.166
Okay, you know,
just go easy on her, okay?

18:56.375 --> 19:00.166
She's not right. I think we both--
We both know that.

19:00.166 --> 19:01.917
You know what I mean?

19:03.750 --> 19:05.625
For you.

19:05.875 --> 19:07.709
Okay.

19:10.542 --> 19:12.583
Why is she not attracted to me?

19:12.583 --> 19:14.291
I think she's stupid. I hate her.

19:15.291 --> 19:18.792
Well, maybe she's not into looks.

19:18.792 --> 19:22.375
You know, maybe...
Maybe she dislikes you

19:22.375 --> 19:23.583
for who you are.

19:24.333 --> 19:26.291
- You think?
- Andrea,

19:26.291 --> 19:30.166
life has a way
of evening things out,

19:30.166 --> 19:33.667
and pretty on the outside usually
doesn't get to be pretty on the inside.

19:34.125 --> 19:39.667
And Andrea you are very,
very pretty on the outside.

19:40.250 --> 19:41.834
Thank you.

19:49.291 --> 19:52.250
I checked my voicemail.
I was turned down for the apartment.

19:52.250 --> 19:55.750
It was a done deal. It was my place.
A crappy place, but it was mine.

19:57.875 --> 19:59.917
You know, um,

20:00.750 --> 20:02.625
you could always just stay here.

20:03.875 --> 20:07.041
- Excuse me?
- Until you find exactly what you want.

20:07.834 --> 20:12.458
Okay, when did we ever worry
about what I wanted?

20:12.458 --> 20:16.458
I know. I know.
I-- It's just I can't explain it entirely.

20:16.458 --> 20:18.583
I just know
that looking over these notes,

20:18.583 --> 20:22.875
everything ends with, uh, "Bad to Todd,"
or "Apologize to Todd,"

20:22.875 --> 20:25.417
or "Buy Todd a new bird."

20:25.417 --> 20:26.417
That was you.

20:27.417 --> 20:30.583
I just think I would feel a lot better
if I could just make it up to you.

20:31.583 --> 20:32.750
So I'd be doing you a favor.

20:33.709 --> 20:34.875
If you wouldn't mind.

20:35.417 --> 20:38.458
- No rent then?
- A favor, not a charity.

20:38.458 --> 20:40.709
But it's just friends, right?

20:40.709 --> 20:44.125
Yeah, of course.
Just as-- Just as friends, you know?

20:44.125 --> 20:46.583
Or not friends
if you don't wanna do that.

20:46.583 --> 20:49.375
We could, you know,
just be roommates.

20:49.375 --> 20:51.542
No, no, no. Friends would be nice.

20:51.542 --> 20:53.709
Because I'll probably slide
on the rent a few times,

20:53.709 --> 20:55.917
and my roommate
might not understand.

21:04.166 --> 21:06.625
SAM: <i>Navigating through memories</i>
<i>can be quite a trip.</i>

21:06.625 --> 21:09.750
<i>And maybe it's true, maybe the mind,</i>
<i>like any smart traveler,</i>

21:09.750 --> 21:13.792
<i>does know where it's safe to go</i>
<i>and where it's not.</i>

21:13.792 --> 21:16.834
<i>At least until the time is right.</i>
